message.content: The midpoint of their coordinates will be the average of their $x$-coordinates and the average of their $y$-coordinates. The average of their $x$-coordinates is $\frac{0+(-4)}{2}=-2$, and the average of their $y$-coordinates is $\frac{7+(-1)}{2}=3$. Therefore, they will meet at $\boxed{(-2,3)}$.
